SIMPLE: touch-needle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Touch-needle
<hw>Touch"-nee`dle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Metal.)</fld>
<def>A small bar of gold and silver, either pure, or alloyed in some
known proportion with copper, for trying the purity of articles of gold
or silver by comparison of the streaks made by the article and the bar
on a touchstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Touch-paper</ent>⟦br⟧
